column5: Does anyone know the status of it post-thanksgiving?  Is it open to the public or does the park shut it down?
Wish I could help Raf dont even know where it is
I don't know either Raf. Maybe if you give this number a call:  Pete's Place boat launch. Address: Near | Parry Sound, ON Tel: 1 705 378-0685
Raf, here is the phone number for Oasler PP who are in charge of the Masassauga, they should be able to tell you. 705-378-2401
You probably know this, but I don't think you'd have a problem launching at the Moon River marina, Raf.
Yup,  They stay open late for the hunting crowd. $20 to launch though... We technically $10 in, and another $10 to come out
it was open the weekend before thanks givin.  i think the sign said it is open till later in the year.  i'm willing to admit i'm wrong though if its not.  the mind was a little fuzzy that weekend.
As a Provincial Park ( the Massassauga) I believe the ramp closes with the Park on Thanksgiving- too bad, they have an awesome ramp!
